The equation of the plane through the points $$(2, - 1, - 3)$$ and parallel to the line,<br><br>$${{x - 1} \over 2} = {{y + 2} \over 3} = {z \over { - 4}}$$ and $${x \over 2} = {{y - 1} \over { - 3}} = {{z - 2} \over 2}$$<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   {x - 2} &amp; {y + 1} &amp; {z + 3}  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow (x - 2)(6 - 12) - (y + 1)(4 + 8) + (z + 3)( - 6 - 6) = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - 6x + 12 - 12y - 12 - 12z - 36 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow  - 6x - 12y - 12z - 36 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x + 2y + 2z + 6 = 0$$

Equation of the plane will be<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   {x - 1} &amp; {y - 2} &amp; {z + 3}  \cr 
   {2 - 1} &amp; { - 2 - 2} &amp; {1 - ( - 3)}  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left| {\matrix{
   {x - 1} &amp; {y - 2} &amp; {z + 3}  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|\, = \,0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 1[4(y - 2) + 4(z + 3)] = 0$$ [Expanding along R<sub>3</sub>]<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 4y - 8 + 4z + 12 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 4y + 4z + 4 = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow y + z + 1 = 0$$
